SUMMARY — What you can and cannot do:

  ALLOWED:
  * Read, share, and link to the documentation.
  * Fork the repository and develop it further for your own purposes.
  * Use or present content in courses, seminars, and lectures
    (universities, schools, etc.).
  * Quote excerpts in non-commercial publications (with attribution).
  * Create and publish translations and adaptations
    — provided they are under the same license.

  NOT ALLOWED:
  * Commercial use — e.g., embedding in paid products,
    hosting behind a paywall, or selling as part of a course.
  * Publishing derivatives under a different license.
  * Removing or obscuring the attribution.

  CONDITIONS:
  * Attribution — The author (kaufco) must be credited in every use.
  * ShareAlike — Derivatives must be published under the same license
    (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).

